{"build_type":"library","description":"As-completed collector event loop: parks on the shared doorbell, dispatches pending work items to worker-runners and harvests ready results, then recurses until the stream is closed, the item queue is drained (head==tail) and completed==launched; then returns. Slice 4.4b-2: after each dispatch it reaps completed workers (non-blocking, reap-completed-worker-slots-across-block-ring state 0); at the termination branch it does a blocking sweep (…state 1) so the last straggler is not leaked. Reorder (footprint): the non-blocking reap now runs BEFORE dispatch each wake, so completed workers' stack/seed/prctx chunks are returned to this (collector) thread's g_arena_free_list first, and dispatch's grab reuses them via Tier-1 first-fit instead of pool-bumping — and the collector never parks mid-dispatch before it has freed memory.","module_name":"drive-collector-event-loop-until-fully-drained","package_name":"drive-collector-event-loop-until-fully-drained","function_definitions":{"drive-collector-event-loop-until-fully-drained":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"state","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"seven","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":7},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"nine","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":9},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eleven","variable_type":"i64","assignment_